data.name: Cinccino

abilities.name: Make Do
abilities.text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Energy Assist
attacks.text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its body secrets oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

data.name: Cinccino

abilities.name: Smooth Coat
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Echoed Voice
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

attacks.name: Tail Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Do the Wave
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the number of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

data.name: Cinccino

attacks.name: Covet
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals his or her hand. Choose a card you find there and put it on the bottom of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Last Resort
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

attacks.name: Sweeping Cure
attacks.text: Heal 90 damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Knock Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

data.flavorText: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

attacks.name: Captivate
attacks.text: Switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fluffy Tail
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.flavorText: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.

attacks.text: Choose 2 cards from your discard pile. Then, ask your opponent if you may put them into your hand. If yes, put those cards into your hand. If no, this attack does 80 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.
